data.title: High-Quality Medical Imaging Dataset for Few-Shot Learning
data.abstract: We present a carefully curated dataset of 500 expert-annotated medical images that achieves state-of-the-art performance with only 10% of the training data compared to existing large-scale datasets. Our strategic selection methodology focuses on quality over quantity, demonstrating that smaller, high-quality datasets can outperform massive collections.

data.title: Limited Data for Climate Modeling: A Scarcity Analysis
data.abstract: Climate modeling faces significant data scarcity challenges due to expensive sensor deployments and privacy restrictions. We analyze how synthetic data generation could address these limitations.
